{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὀδῠν-η</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>pain of body,</b> ὀδύνῃσι κακῇσι τειρόμενος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.440, compare 415, 17.567; ἀλεγεινή 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.398 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὀδύναι δῦνον μένος Ἀτρείδαο[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 268; ὀδύνῃσι πεπαρμένος 5.399; ἀντίτομα στερεᾶν ὀδυνᾶν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.221; compare ἕρμα 1.4; στρόφος μ᾽ ἔχει τὴν γαστέρ᾽.. κὠδύνη 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 484, compare “Pl.” 1131: also in Prose, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 5.4.58 (_plural_), 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 9.11.3, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>pain of mind, grief, distress,</b> once in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad”, ὀ. Ἡρακλῆος\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <b>grief for</b> him, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 15.25: more frequently in 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey”, \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] always in <i>plural</i>, ὀδύνας τε γόους τε κάλλιπεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1.242; ὀδύνας ἐμβάλλετε θυμῷ 2.79, +others: after 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus the _plural_ was most common in both senses, ὀ. δυσαπάλλακτοι, ἄλληκτοι, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 959, 986 (both Lyric poetry); ὀδύναις πεφυσιγγωμένοι 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 526 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to φιλότητες, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Sophista 49; σφαδᾳσμῶν τε καὶ ὀδυνῶν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 579e, compare 574a, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: but the <i>singular</i>also occurs, ἐξ ὀλίγης ὀ. μέγα γίνεται ἄλγος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus 12.59 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; γλώσσας ὀ. <b>pain caused by</b> the tongue, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1142, compare 827 (both Lyric poetry), “Tr.” 975 (_anapaest meter_); ὀ. σε εἴληφε 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 1.15; ὀ. μ᾽ ἔχει “Lyrica Alexandrina Adespota” 1.3; μετ᾽ ὀδύνης 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 706 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοῖς νενικημένοις ὀδύνη,=Latin <i>vae victis!</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Camillus” 28. (Perh. from ἐδ- ὀδ- 'eat',compare θυμὸν ἔδων 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.379: the Aeolians called τὰς ὀδύνας ἐδύνας _accusative_ to Greg.Cor. p.597 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3601","accentedUnicode":"ὀδύνη","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3600","matchingForm":"ὀδυνάω","stepTransliteration":"odunaō","gloss":"be anguished","_zh_tw_Gloss":"受痛苦, 傷心","_es_Gloss":"estar angustiado","_zh_Gloss":"受痛苦, 伤心"},{"strongNumber":"G5604","matchingForm":"ὠδίν","stepTransliteration":"ōdin","gloss":"labor","_zh_tw_Gloss":"產難","_es_Gloss":"dolores de parto","_zh_Gloss":"产难"}],"shortDef":"anguish, grief, pain","mediumDef":"anguish, grief, pain <br /><b>pain</b>, of body of mind; <b>sorrow, grief,</b> <ref='Rom.9.2'>Rom. 9:2;</ref> <ref='1Ti.6.10'>1Tim. 6:10</ref>*","stepGloss":"anguish","stepTransliteration":"odunē","count":2,"_es_Definition":"dolor, pena","_zh_tw_Definition":"傷痛, 悲傷(羅 9:2; #提前 6:10)","_zh_Definition":"伤痛, 悲伤(罗 9:2; #提前 6:10)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự đau đớn; sự lo lắng; sự đau khổ","_zh_tw_Gloss":"愁苦","_es_Gloss":"angustia","_zh_Gloss":"愁苦"}]}